6:
Kohane? Hurry up or we'll leave
without you.
16:
...Is your leg okay? It looks like you're
having trouble walking.
20:
Dunno. It don't hurt or nothin', but for
some reason whenever I walk, it
feels weird.
24:
I don't like the sound of that. We
should get it checked right away!
29:
D-don't look at me like that! The
more YOU worry about it, the more
I'M gonna worry...
35:
All right, both of you calm down.
Kohane, take a look at your shoes.
The wooden things on the bottom
are different heights.
40:
Oh, NO! You're right! One of my geta
is worn down a TON. No wonder it
was hard to walk.
46: The wood certainly looks... worn in.
48:
You can just call 'em "old as all
heck," I won't mind.
51:
Master gave them to me. See, I
wanted somethin' trendy and
sporty, but nooo. It's tengu tradition
to blah blah blah.
54:
It is an honor to be entrusted with
generations of history. Tradition
should not be taken so—
56:
Oh. Key. Dokey. Never mention
"tradition" to Light ever again, noted.
60:
I'm too cute to walk around lookin'
like someone's
great-great-grandma!
66:
Hmm... Nothing wrong with having a
little variety in your wardrobe.
67:
Let's at least get you some new
shoes before you hurt yourself.
Sound good?
72:
Sounds great! Oh man, I'm gonna
be so CUTE! Gonna make all them
city folk jealous!
77:
Wh-what's goin' on?! I never seen so
many people all in one spot!
81:
The market's having a huge sale
today, so everyone's out bargain
hunting.
84:
Catch the freshest deals at Flipper's
Fishmarket! All fish are 50% off! You
heard me, 50% OFF ALL FISH!
86:
Fish? Pshhh. Today's your chance to
splurge on quality meats, for just a
fraction of the price! Venison, veal,
goose! All 80% off!
91:
Oooh, this looks so fun! What else've
they got—
106: I'm seein' a lot of frowny faces.
110:
Can't have that now, can we?
C'mere, you.
125: Do it again! I wanna turn!
135:
There you are. We heard you've had
quite the afternoon.
139:
I flew some people around, and they
gave me this. All of it! Can ya believe
it?
143: Those look like, uh... offerings, huh?
148:
Ooh, look! Someone left me a pair of
boots!
149:
They're so cute! Is it really okay for
me to take 'em?
154: Perfect timing. Why not try them on?
157:
Yeah! My first step into the world of
fashion... Look out Palpebra, here I—
Huh?
159:
Markie! Goodness, I've been looking
all over for you!
161:
Mom! Mom, guess what! This lady
was waiting with me, and we were
playing, and she can FLY!
163:
Fly? ...Thank you for keeping an eye
on him, dear.
165:
See ya 'round! You've gotta teach
me how to fly too next time, okay?
173:
...Anyways, do the boots look the
right size?
177:
You know... Maybe I'll save 'em for
some other time. My geta aren't
broken, so if I just whittle 'em down
to be the same height, they'll work
fine.
181:
Wouldn't want Master thinkin' I can't
take proper care of my stuff!
184:
More importantly, I'm starved from
all that flyin'! Let's go grab
something to eat!
189:
Yeah... Is there anything specific you
had in mind?
194:
Is there? Is there EVER! The girls were
tellin' me about this "boba" tea stuff
and y'all it sounds AWESOME!
198:
Ahaha, I know a little café near here.
Super trendy, veeery stylish, totally
up your alley.
